<TITLE> IFC wants to invest in farm, infrastructure </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 3 (bdnews24.com)  The International Finance Corporation has expressed interest to invest in agriculture and infrastructure sectors, the central bank chief said Sunday. Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed had a meeting with a visiting six-strong IFC delegation led by executive vice president Lars Henrik Thunell at his office. He later told reporters that the development partner of the World Bank wanted to work with the government in addition to contributing to the private sector. Asked about the higher interest rate of the IFC, the governor said there would be discussion to reduce interest rate. World Bank resident representative Xian Zeo, Bangladesh Bank deputy governor Ziaul Hasan Siddiqui and executive director Yasin Ali were also present at the meeting. bdnews
